{"version":"2.0","class":"dataset","label":"HICP - monthly data (annual rate of change) (1997-2025)","source":"ESTAT","updated":"2026-02-06T23:00:00+0100","value":{"0":2.8,"1":2.6,"2":2.3,"3":2.2,"4":2.1,"5":2.0,"6":1.8,"7":2.1,"8":2.4,"9":2.3,"10":2.6,"11":2.0,"12":1.8,"13":0.9,"14":0.9,"15":0.9,"16":0.6,"17":0.9,"18":0.9,"19":0.8,"20":1.1,"21":0.8,"22":0.8,"23":0.7},"id":["freq","unit","coicop","geo","time"],"size":[1,1,1,3,12],"dimension":{"freq":{"label":"Time frequency","category":{"index":{"M":0},"label":{"M":"Monthly"}}},"unit":{"label":"Unit of measure","category":{"index":{"RCH_A":0},"label":{"RCH_A":"Annual rate of change"}}},"coicop":{"label":"Classification of individual consumption by purpose (COICOP)","category":{"index":{"CP00":0},"label":{"CP00":"All-items HICP"}}},"geo":{"label":"Geopolitical entity (reporting)","category":{"index":{"DE":0,"FR":1,"US":2},"label":{"DE":"Germany","FR":"France","US":"United States"}}},"time":{"label":"Time","category":{"index":{"2025-01":0,"2025-02":1,"2025-03":2,"2025-04":3,"2025-05":4,"2025-06":5,"2025-07":6,"2025-08":7,"2025-09":8,"2025-10":9,"2025-11":10,"2025-12":11},"label":{"2025-01":"2025-01","2025-02":"2025-02","2025-03":"2025-03","2025-04":"2025-04","2025-05":"2025-05","2025-06":"2025-06","2025-07":"2025-07","2025-08":"2025-08","2025-09":"2025-09","2025-10":"2025-10","2025-11":"2025-11","2025-12":"2025-12"}}}},"extension":{"lang":"EN","description":"<p>The Harmonised Index of Consumer Prices (HICP) measures price changes of various consumer goods and services over time (inflation). The annual rate of change is the percentage change in one month compared to the same month of the previous year, also called annual inflation. It is calculated from the monthly indices and rounded to one decimal place.&nbsp;</p><p>Please note that this dataset is discontinued and replaced by dataset <a href=\"https://ec.europa.eu/eurostat/databrowser/bookmark/60ebcdf2-9eb8-4901-b98e-46b62b318ea4?lang=en&amp;createdAt=2026-05-20T13: